Ren&#233; Roman was last seen leaving her Lavender Hill home to go to a nearby shop last Friday. CAPE TOWN - The Steenberg community policing forum (CPF) says it remains positive as efforts to find a missing 13-year-old girl continue.Ren Roman was last seen leaving her Lavender Hill home to go to a nearby shop last Friday. Romans mother says the girl was taken by someone but no further details are available.The CPF s Lucinda Evans says: We are still very hopeful like I told the people today, we are looking for Rene and not a body. The community is supporting her parents. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)